if any1 tinks it works i try it[/quote]Your computer’s internet IP has changed. This is different from your COMPUTER IP address.

Follow my steps:
Before anything, make sure you portforwarded any new firewalls on your computer and such.

  1. Go to http://no-ip.org
  2. Log in
  3. Go to hosts/redirects
  4. Click ‘modify’ (located on the right of the IP address you are using)
  5. Where you see the IP address in a box, replace that with the ip address that is listed under your name on the top right-hand corner of the screen.
  6. Save the changes to the IP
  7. Wait 5-10 minutes, then try to log in with that No-IP Address.
